The paper deals with algorithms for solving extensive-form games, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (AI) and game theory (GT). The use of baseline estimates to reduce variance is a common technique in machine learning (ML) and reinforcement learning (RL), which are subfields of AI. The paper also discusses the use of Monte Carlo methods, which are commonly used in ML and statistics (DS). Finally, the paper deals with multi-agent interactions, which are studied in the field of multi-agent systems (MA).
